{"title_page": "Mauritian of British origin", "text_new": "{{Short description|ethnic group}}\n{{refimprove|date=August 2015}}\n{{Infobox ethnic group\n|group      = British Mauritian\n| image =\n{{image array|perrow=2|width=65|height=85\n| image1 = Rav Wilding TV Presenter.jpg| caption1  = [[Rav Wilding]]\n| image2 = Thomas Blackburn.jpg| caption2  = [[Thomas Blackburn]]\n}}\n|population = \n|languages  = {{hlist| [[Mauritian creole|Creole]]|[[English language|English]]  }}\n|religions  = [[Anglican Church]], Others\n|related    = \n|related-c  =  \n|footnotes  = \n}}\n\nA '''Mauritian of British origin''', as the name implies, is a [[Mauritians|Mauritian]] person whose ancestors are from the British Islands: [[United Kingdom]]. All members of such group is usually identified as a '''British-Mauritian'''.\n\n==Origins==\nPeople of [[British people|British]] Origin in [[Mauritius]] Island.\n\n==Demographic factors==\nBritish-Mauritians comprise 1% of the population of Mauritius<ref>http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/shared/spl/hi/in_depth/brits_abroad/html/</ref>\n\nMost Franco-Mauritians are Anglican Church.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Mauritian of Indian origin]]\n* [[Mauritian of African origin]]\n* [[White Mauritians|Mauritian of European origin]]\n* [[Mauritian of Chinese origin]]\n* [[Mauritian Creole]]\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{Mauritius topics}}\n{{British diaspora}}\n\n[[Category:Mauritian people of British descent| ]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in Mauritius]]\n[[Category:British diaspora by country|Mauritius]]\n\n\n{{Mauritius-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|ethnic group}}\n{{refimprove|date=August 2015}}\n{{Infobox ethnic group\n|group      = British Mauritian\n| image =\n{{image array|perrow=2|width=65|height=85\n| image1 = Rav Wilding TV Presenter.jpg| caption1  = [[Rav Wilding]]\n| image2 = Thomas Blackburn.jpg| caption2  = [[Thomas Blackburn]]\n}}\n|population = \n|languages  = {{hlist| [[Mauritian creole|Creole]]|[[English language|English]]  }}\n|religions  = [[Anglican Church]], Others\n|related    = \n|related-c  =  \n|footnotes  = \n}}\n\nA '''Mauritian of British origin''', as the name implies, is a [[Mauritians|Mauritian]] person whose ancestors are from the British Islands: [[United Kingdom]]. All members of such group is usually identified as a '''British-Mauritian'''.\n\n==Origins==\nPeople of [[British]] Origin in [[Mauritius]] Island.\n\n==Demographic factors==\nBritish-Mauritians comprise 1% of the population of Mauritius<ref>http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/shared/spl/hi/in_depth/brits_abroad/html/</ref>\n\nMost Franco-Mauritians are Anglican Church.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Mauritian of Indian origin]]\n* [[Mauritian of African origin]]\n* [[White Mauritians|Mauritian of European origin]]\n* [[Mauritian of Chinese origin]]\n* [[Mauritian Creole]]\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n{{Mauritius topics}}\n{{British diaspora}}\n\n[[Category:Mauritian people of British descent| ]]\n[[Category:Ethnic groups in Mauritius]]\n[[Category:British diaspora by country|Mauritius]]\n\n\n{{Mauritius-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toBritish(link changed toBritish people) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mauritian_of_British_origin"}
