        = [[12th Regiment Royal Artillery]] \n | commands        = \n | battles         = \n | mawards         =  <!-- for military awards - appears as \"Awards\" if |awards= is not set -->\n | military_blank1 = \n | military_data1  = \n | military_blank2 = \n | military_data2  = \n | military_blank3 = \n | military_data3  = \n | military_blank4 = \n | military_data4  = \n | military_blank5 = \n | military_data5  = \n<!--Embedded templates / Footnotes-->\n | module          = \n | module2         = \n | module3         = \n | module4         = \n | module5         = \n | footnotes       = \n}}\n\nCommissioner '''Andy Roe''' is a former [[British Army]] officer currently serving as the [[Commissioner of the London Fire Brigade]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-london-50727812|title=New fire chief appointed after Grenfell row|date=December 10, 2019|via=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and education ==\nAndy Roe grew up in London and graduated from [[Newcastle University]] in 1995 with a [[Bachelor of Arts]] in [[English literature]].\n\n== Career ==\nIn 1996, Andy Roe commissioned out of [[Royal Military Academy Sandhurst]] to join the [[12th Regiment Royal Artillery]] as an officer and in his time as an officer, he served as a troop commander and a battery captain and served two tours in [[Northern Ireland]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.london-fire.gov.uk/about-us/meet-london-fire-brigade/andy-roe-commissioner/|title=Andy Roe, Commissioner|website=www.london-fire.gov.uk}}</ref>\n\nIn 2002, Andy Roe joined the London Fire Brigade as a firefighter<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.insidehousing.co.uk/news/news/grenfell-fire-officer-who-ordered-evacuation-named-new-lfb-chief--64480|title=Grenfell fire officer who ordered evacuation named new LFB chief|website=Inside Housing}}</ref> and in January of 2017 was appointed as [[Assistant commissioner|Assistant Commissioner]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forces.net/news/former-army-officer-becomes-new-london-fire-chief|title=Former Army Officer Becomes New London Fire Chief|first=11th December 2019|last=at 2:28pm|website=Forces Network}}</ref>\n\nDuring the [[Grenfell Tower fire]], Andy Roe was appointed incident commander where he revoked the controversial 'stay put' advice to the residents.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/andy-roe-grenfell-firefighter-who-revoked-stay-put-policy-is-new-london-fire-brigade-boss-11883030|title=Andy Roe: Grenfell firefighter who revoked 'stay put' policy is new London Fire Brigade boss|website=Sky News}}</ref> As the first commissioner appointed since the fire, Commissioner Roe issued a plea to the residents of London's 7000 high rise blocks to set aside any 'post-Grenfell doubts continue to follow firefighters\u2019 advice in the event of a blaze.'<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/london/andy-roe-london-fire-commissioner-grenfell-a4379161.html|title=New London fire chief\u2019s first job: to say sorry over Grenfell|date=March 5, 2020|website=Evening Standard}}</ref>\n\nOn the 28th of January 2020, Andy Roe became the first LFB commissioner to sign a covenant with the [[British Armed Forces]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fsmatters.com/LFB-sign-covenant-UK-Armed-Forces|title=FSM MAGAZINE - LFB fire commissioner signs covenant with UK Armed Forces|website=www.fsmatters.com}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and Honours ==\n\n<center>\n[[File:QEII Diamond Jubilee Medal ribbon.png|100px]]\n[[File:General_Service_Medal_1962_BAR.svg|100px]]\n</center>\n\n<center>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:silver;\" align=\"center\"\n|Ribbon || Description || Notes\n|-\n|[[File:QEII Diamond Jubilee Medal ribbon.png|40px]] || [[Queen Elizabeth II Diamond Jubilee Medal]] ||\n* 2012\n* UK Version of this Medal\n|-\n|[[File:General_Service_Medal_1962_BAR.svg|40px]] || [[General Service Medal (1962)]] ||\n*For Service in Northern Ireland\n|-\n|}\n</center>\n\n==See also==\n*[[London Fire Brigade]]\n*[[Chief Fire Officer]]\n*[[London Fire and Emergency Planning Authority]]\n*[[Chief Fire Officers Association]]\n\n== References == \n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:London Fire Brigade officers]]\n[[Category:People associated with the Royal Military Academy Sandhurst]]\n", "text_old": "\n\n{{Infobox officeholder\n | honorific_prefix   = [[Commissioner of the London Fire Brigade|Commissioner]]\n | name               = Andy Roe\n | native_name        = <!--The person's name in their own language, if different.-->\n | native_name_lang   = <!--ISO 639-1 code, e.g., \"fr\" for French. If more than one, use {{lang}} in |native_name= instead.-->\n | honorific_suffix   = \n | image              = \n | image_size         = \n | image_upright      = \n | smallimage         = <!--If this is specified, \"image\" should not be.-->\n | alt                = \n | caption            = \n | order              = \n | office             = [[Commissioner of the London Fire Brigade]]\n | status             = <!--If this is specified, overrides Incumbent.-->\n | term_start         = January 2020\n | term_end           = <!-- Add data only when the actual term has ended, not for terms which will end in the future. (Per usage guideline.) -->\n | alongside          = <!--For two or more people serving in the same position from the same district.  (e.g. United States Senators.)-->\n | monarch            = [[HM Queen Elizabeth II]]\n | president          = \n | governor_general   = \n | primeminister      = [[Boris Johnson]]\n | governor           = \n | chair              = \n | vicepresident      = \n | viceprimeminister  = \n | deputy             = \n | lieutenant         = \n | vicechair          = \n | succeeding         = <!--For President-elect or equivalent-->\n | parliamentarygroup = \n | constituency       = \n | majority           = \n | predecessor        = [[Dany Cotton]]\n | successor          = \n | prior_term         = \n | order2             =  <!--Can be repeated up to 16 times by changing