ation named new LFB chief|website=Inside Housing}}</ref> and in January of 2017 was appointed as [[Assistant commissioner|Assistant Commissioner]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forces.net/news/former-army-officer-becomes-new-london-fire-chief|title=Former Army Officer Becomes New London Fire Chief|first=11th December 2019|last=at 2:28pm|website=Forces Network}}</ref>\n\nDuring the [[Grenfell Tower fire]], Andy Roe was appointed incident commander where he revoked the controversial 'stay put' advice to the residents.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.sky.com/story/andy-roe-grenfell-firefighter-who-revoked-stay-put-policy-is-new-london-fire-brigade-boss-11883030|title=Andy Roe: Grenfell firefighter who revoked 'stay put' policy is new London Fire Brigade boss|website=Sky News}}</ref> As the first commissioner appointed since the fire, Commissioner Roe issued a plea to the residents of London's 7000 high rise blocks to set aside any 'post-Grenfell doubts continue to follow firefighters\u2019 advice in the event of a blaze.'<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/london/andy-roe-london-fire-commissioner-grenfell-a4379161.html|title=New London fire chief\u2019s first job: to say sorry over Grenfell|date=March 5, 2020|website=Evening Standard}}</ref>\n\nOn the 28th of January 2020, Andy Roe became the first LFB commissioner to sign a covenant with the [[British Armed Forces]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fsmatters.com/LFB-sign-covenant-UK-Armed-Forces|title=FSM MAGAZINE - LFB fire commissioner signs covenant with UK Armed Forces|website=www.fsmatters.com}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and Honours ==\n\n<center>\n[[File:QEII Diamond Jubilee Medal ribbon.png|100px]]\n[[File:General_Service_Medal_1962_BAR.svg|100px]]\n</center>\n\n<center>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- style=\"background:silver;\" align=\"center\"\n|Ribbon || Description || Notes\n|-\n|[[File:QEII Diamond Jubilee Medal ribbon.png|40px]] || [[Queen Elizabeth II Diamond Jubilee Medal]] ||\n* 2012\n* UK Vers